{
  "stem": "27507.11",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And one of us, this German chap who could speak well German, he sometimes appeared upstairs and spoke to the soldiers, but the soldiers didn't-- obviously, they were noticed as they were not interested in exactly who it was that still was there.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "But we didn't have-- we didn't have-- there was nobody there except for the soldiers, and we were under-- that was all under artillery fire.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "The Germans were shooting from the west and the Russians were shooting from the east, so it was not exactly cozy.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And there was nothing to eat, either, because the food was-- by then, any food that we had was finished, and there was no food to be had.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the only food that we could find was because there were [INAUDIBLE] gardens.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were some vegetables growing there and growing in the zoological garden, which was-- which was quite near, in fact, where there were no animals, but where it was all planted with things like potatoes and cabbage and beetroot and so on.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we had still some food.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The food was-- in the night, some men were going out and finding some vegetables, and we were eating that, although there was very little of it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on my birthday again, in the end of August, I think my father got some tomatoes for me, which was a great feast because that was so unbelievable that you could get some tomatoes.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we're getting quite hungry, but because there was no bread, there were just those vegetables.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Potatoes-- there were few potatoes, so we were living on those, on some potatoes and on some other vegetables.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in this way-- and then in September, the front was coming.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Came near it again.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
